                    <tr>
           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000">
                      <font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Ok, the latest changes are on <b><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/newspells.html?source=Test&date=2003-07-30%2022:34:46" target="_blank">Lucy</a></b>.<br /><br /><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spellhistory.html?id=4081&source=Test" target="_blank">A couple of name changes for the pet buff.</a><br /><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spellhistory.html?id=4100&source=Test" target="_blank">Little changes for the "Reflect" spell.</a><br /><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spellhistory.html?id=4098&source=Test" target="_blank">Most Importantly the curse line was changed a bit.</a><br /><br />To sum it up, the duration was changed to 5 ticks (so it can be focused), the damage was increased a little bit (less per tick, more overall). <br />Now this is all fine and good, but the only problem I still see with these line of spells are their horrible mana/dmg ratios. A 3.45 efficency <i>conjuration</i> based spell with no resist adjustment. Blood of Thule at least has a ratio of 4.69. That, combined with an overall low dmg (for 80 more mana we can cast blood of thule and do 225 more dmg in the five ticks). Not to mention if the mob would last longer blood of thule would do even more dmg. I think they had the right idea with the <a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=4095&source=Test" target="_blank">shaman curse spell</a>. Good total dmg with a improved efficiency. These seem to be nuke/dots, but their efficency is lower then most of the nukes! Neurotoxin is the worst efficency of course, but most high end nukes come with a efficency of at least 4. Wizard nukes go even higher. This spell, while an excellent attempt at providing us with short quick dots, instead provides us with lesser versions of our longer dots.<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font>
           	</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td valign="bottom"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> <b><i><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=182018" target="_blank">Lich Sadista Elvenbane</a></i></b><br />Arch Lich of <a href="http://www.orderofthephoenix.com" target="_blank">Order of the Phoenix</a><br />Saryrn Server</span></font></td>
