                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Good thing you posted that here then... Gurthel.<br /><br />AS for the dots, I think they're an awesome idea.  With short duration dots, we can do some dmg to mobs without wasting 1/4-/1/3 of our mana cost for a dot.  I'm using VOS in some situations now just to do all the dmg.<br /><br />Lets look at evenomed bolt... It's only 1k or so dmg, and takes 320 mana. If we get these short dur dots, lets assume they'll be able to do 1k as well, over 5 ticks, that's 200 dmg per tick.  I use evenomed bolt as an example, because our other dots similar in level and dmg to it but w/ longer duration cost less mana.<br /><br />If we're going to get quick dots, they'll have to be un-efficient compared to our 2min-1min dots.<br /><br />You could argue that wizards get awesome dmg ratio for nukes 5 to 1 or better.  But they should... Yes, they should. (I'm saying that)<br /><br />For one, Wizards are COMPLETELY dependant on nukes, what else can they do?<br /><br />Necros are given pets, heals, lifetaps, dots, nukes, (snare/root) like wizzies, mez, charm, slow. All these things.  It's FAIR to have penaltys on spells for us, we're too UBER!  We NEED To have the mana cost unfair, because it's the only way we can have a balanced class w/ others.<br /><br />Necros are given the ability to DOT now for short single pulls in groups or whatever.  I say this is awesome, regardless of the conj base, recast time, mana etc.<br /><br />First off, what's the point of having all your spells be based on abjuration? So you don't have to lose more mana? Please.  You know 3/5 based dots are conj based, why Cry about it? Because you can?<br /><br />Sure, it might be fun to have a dot that deathtouches every tick, but what do you expect? To be turned into some GOD because you can whine on a message board. Shutup. I hate you people.<br /><br />Next, resist check... You're saying considering it's a curse spell, the mob should get debuffed, -50 to all stats? And a Malo effect? Why not Ice comet DD while you're at it, OR!!! Mana drain and LIfetap dot, for 56k. Sure, that'd be great.  I'll agree that I wish I had an upgrade of Scent of Terr, but I like things complicated and difficult... I think most necros do, ask a soloing necro.<br /><br />Recast time is irrelevant... If you're in a group, and you land this spell on the mob, you're not going to cast it again.  And lets say it gets resisted or an add comes, Well, You're the most VERSITILE class in the game, I think you can find a substitute strategy from Stand/cast/pet/sit.<br /><br />As for the 3k dot... Real quick, WE ALL KNOW that Shammys have always out-dotted us with ONE spell.  However, the point of a necro, or the power, is in the stacking of several dots.  I do agree w/ the being able to FD off agro rather than not generate it. BUt it really ISN"T hard to get it, if you want it, you'll get it. If not, you're nuking yourself.<br /><br />Again, I'll agree that this spell being low resist would be nice.  But I trust the people that make sure these spells work.  This is a big deal to have, and many seasoned necros are putting their advice into some influential heads.<br /><br />I'd like the spell to look like this, 1.5k dmg, 5 ticks, 350-450 mana conj based, Cold based.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
