ana ratio. BoT has a 4.69 ratio. DP has a 6.2 ratio. ED has a ratio of 7. None of those are horrible ratios. The lack of an alteration effect on them makes very little difference. However, throw in Horror with a ratio of 3.45 and the lack of a good specialization, and the fact that its duration makes it unaffected by affliction efficiency, makes it so it will stay at 3.45. <br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Recast time is irrelevant... If you're in a group, and you land this spell on the mob, you're not going to cast it again. And lets say it gets resisted or an add comes, Well, You're the most VERSITILE class in the game, I think you can find a substitute strategy from Stand/cast/pet/sit.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />With no resist adjustmant and a long recast time this spell will end up being resisted and unable to cast. One or the other plz, not both. No resist adjustment is fine, but take away the recast. Long recast if fine, but plz let it not be resisted when we cast it then.<br /><br /><br /> <br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
